<seg id=1> China Insurance Supervision and Management Project Starts in Beijing </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, January 21 - With the purposes to assist People's Bank of China to perform supervision and management to the insurance laws and regulations made to foreign funded insurance institutions in China, to explore the insurance normalization system and relative measures, a research project was started a few days ago in Beijing. </seg>
<seg id=3> This project was jointly financed by British Royal & Sun Alliance Insurance Group and Lincoln National Group of U.S., and undertaken by Coopers & Lybrand Accounting Firm of U.S. with a total investment of 1.4 million US Dollars. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> This supervision and management project will do systematically analysis on foreign funded insurance in China and existing insurance supervision and management laws and regulations, use foreign experience for reference, make a constructive research scheme to facilitate the development of China's insurance supervision and management and to perfect the supervision and management laws and regulations. </seg>
<seg id=5> The insurance supervision and management project started this time will be based on the existing insurance supervision and management laws and regulations of the People's Bank of China on foreign funded insurance institutions, to do a research more thoroughly and dedicate to strengthen the insurance institution structure and operation procedures, particularly for the development of early stage warning system. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> It is known that the new supervision and management laws and regulations will perfect the existing supervision and management laws and regulations on foreign funded insurance institutions on China market, and assist the People's Bank of China to strengthen its supervision and management system for the whole insurance market. </seg>
</p>
